This paper deals with distributed algorithms in radio networks, which are a type of ad hoc network. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also involves communication and networking, which suggests the category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The use of randomized protocols and analysis of their efficiency suggests the category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also involves information theory and communication complexity, which suggests the category cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper involves the design of energy-efficient algorithms, which suggests the category cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
